import {Component, OnInit} from '@angular/core'; import {Router} from "@angular/router"; import AuthenticationService from "../../../../services/AuthenticationService"; import ThemeService, {EThemeOptions} from "../../../../services/ThemeService"; import User, {EUserRoles} from "../../../../../models/User"; @Component({ selector: 'app-navbar', templateUrl: './navbar.component.html', styleUrls: ['./navbar.component.scss'] }) export class NavbarComponent implements OnInit { protected user: User | null = null; constructor( protected router: Router, protected authentication_service: AuthenticationService, protected theme_service: ThemeService ) { } ngOnInit() { this.user = this.authentication_service.getUser(); this.authentication_service.getUserObserver().subscribe({ next: (new_user: User | null) => { this.user = new_user; }, error: (error) => { this.user = null; } }); } protected parseUserRoles(): String | undefined { return this.user?.getRoles()?.toString().split(',').map((role) => { return role[0] + role.toLowerCase().slice(1, role.length); }).join(', ').replace('None', ''); } protected readonly EThemeOptions = EThemeOptions; protected readonly ERoles = EUserRoles; }
